  "prompt": "What will be one word for \"make an example of\" idiom?",
  "response": "A suitable single word that captures the essence of the idiom \"make an example of\" is **\"punish.\"**\n\nWhile \"punish\" broadly means to impose a penalty or consequence, in the context of \"making an example of\" someone, it implies that the punishment serves not only to address the individual's actions but also to deter others from similar behavior. \n\n**Example in a sentence:**\n- The manager decided to **punish** the employee publicly to discourage others from violating company policies.\n\nIf you're looking for a word that more specifically emphasizes the deterrent aspect, \"deterrence\" is a noun that fits, but \"punish\" remains the most direct single-word equivalent.",
